# calculator.tsx requirements

- First line: `'use client'`.
- **Instant calculation** on input change — NO submit button.
- Explicit `interface` for props and a typed state shape. No `any`.
- Validate inputs. Until inputs are valid, show a friendly placeholder message —
  never render `NaN`, `$NaN`, or `Infinity`.
- Copy-to-clipboard on the primary result (with an `aria-label`).
- Metric/Imperial (or relevant unit) toggle when the domain calls for it.
- Mobile-first layout; include a results breakdown table when it aids understanding
  (e.g. amortization, macro split).
- Accessibility: every input has an associated `<label>`, icon-only buttons have
  `aria-label`, use semantic HTML.
- Use shadcn/ui primitives (`Input`, `Button`, `Tabs`, `Table`, `Slider`). Keep the
  component reusable and presentational where possible.
- Format money/numbers with `Intl.NumberFormat`, not manual string concatenation.
- Keep heavy math in pure helper functions (easy to unit-test); the component just
  wires state to UI.
